### Task 1 润色版

> The flow chart illustrates the main stages involved in producing fabric from bamboo.
>
> Overall, the process consists of several key stages, beginning with the planting of bamboo and ending with the weaving of fabric.
>
> At the beginning, bamboo plants are planted in spring. After two growing seasons, the plants are mature enough to be harvested in autumn by workers. Once harvesting is complete, the bamboo is transported to a workshop, where it is cut into thin strips. These strips are then crushed to produce liquid pulp.
